column60: 'Socially distant birthday'- made a birthday poster for my sister and sang happy birthday to her from the sidewalk outside her house. Also had a 'socially distant Easter picnic' with our parents, where we all brought our own picnic baskets and blankets, sat 10 feet apart, and enjoyed our own separate picnics 'together'. The third time we left our house was to go to 'church'- we went to our church building late in the evening when no one would be there and stood outside the building in the parking lot to pray. This was really nice because we still got to enjoy our house of worship (granted, it was from the outside) but we were able to avoid any contact with any other people.
